-----------------------------------------------------------------------
	   OSACombat Version: 4.1.15 (May 27, 2026)
	
	   Usage:
	   
       osacombat setup                       Opens the setup window to configure combat routines
       osacombat help                        Opens the help window (This window).
       osacombat ?                           Opens the help window (This window).
	   
       * Note: All commands can be initiated while the script is running. (Do not use semi-colon for commands while running OSACombat)
	   
       OSACombat is an automated combat script.
       Enjoy 
		
       ~Peggyanne 
       
	   PS: feel free to send me any bugs via discord Bait#4376 and I'll try my best to fix them.
	 
	 Change Log:
	 
              May 24, 2025 - Improved Targeting Logic, Removed Attack Types and Added Use Archery and Use UAC W/O Weapons Checkboxes.
               June 7, 2025 - Removed Anti Effect methods, Ecleanse does this much better. Also fixed logic for assaults.
              June 19, 2025 - Resolved Lag and Redundancy Issues. Also Added Support for Paladin Feat Excoriate.
              June 22, 2025 - Adjusted Opener Spell Logic, Added Opener Support For Cold Snap And Added A Second Opener Spell.
              June 23, 2025 - Fixed Targeting Error In Second Spell Opener.
              July 19, 2025 - Fixed Issue With Unstun Method That Was Causing Lag.
              July 20, 2025 - Fixed Issue With Mob Count If Statements.
              July 26, 2025 - Adjusted Assaults And Removed Spell Active Check.
              July 30, 2025 - Added 611 To Openers Check.
             August 3, 2025 - Added 1650 Armor For Emergency Use And 1650 Zeal To Support Tab.
            August 18, 2025 - Added Second AOE And Assaults, Added Support For Flare Gloves Pound Feature And Added Auto Looting Depending On Weekly/Monthly Gemstone Finds (Uses Killtracker).
            August 23, 2025 - Added Self Cast Versions Of Barkskin And Added Self And Group Celerity To Buffs.
            August 31, 2025 - Added Checkbox For 330 Evoke For Both Hands And Improved Anti-Poaching Logic.
         September 6, 2025 - Fixed Minor Error In Anti-Poaching Logic.
        September 21, 2025 - Yet Again More Changes To Anti-Poaching and Hiding Group Member Logic.
        September 25, 2025 - Even More Anti-Poaching Fixes.
        September 26, 2025 - Removed Unnecessary Targeting, Changed Default Healing Room and Added Stance Dancing Toggle.
          December 6, 2025 - Added Gemstone Support, Removed Vars Dependancy, Added Yaml Support, Added Tooltips and Default Values.
          December 8, 2025 - Bug Fixes On Surge Of Strength and Warcry Targeting.
         December 13, 2025 - Fixed Upstream Toggle and Error Message.
         December 28, 2025 - Fixed Targeting Issue With Unearthly Chains and Evanescent Possession.
           January 2, 2026 - Fixed Minor Error In RT Management For Some Cmans.
          January 12, 2026 - Fixed Minor Logic Error In Buff Startup.
          January 17, 2026 - Added Stomp and Pound Options For 909.
          January 25, 2026 - Added Anti-Poaching Command For Toggle and Changed Name of Setup Method To Prevent Cross Script Errors.
          February 1, 2026 - Updated Yaml Read/Write Methods To Include FLOCK Operations To Prevent Data Corruption.
         February 13, 2026 - Rewrote YAML Config and GTK3 Using AI. Added Min Stamina/Mana And Maximum Enemy Count Thresholds.
         February 16, 2026 - Added Support For Energy Wings Offensive Abilities.
         February 21, 2026 - Added Upstream Hooks For Help And Setup. Converted All Dropdowns To Strings Instead Of Integers.
         February 27, 2026 - Fixed Targetting Issue. Targetting Will Default To Undead Routine If Any Undead Are Present. Upstream Hook Parsing Issue Resolved.
           April 11, 2026 - Fixed Targetting Issues Temporarily Until Rewrite Using More Sound Logic.
           April 19, 2026 - More Targetting Issues Resolved.
             May 16, 2026 - Fixed spell 610 room effect guard false-matching decorative room objects. Added Opener Spell slots (3 per tab). Added Skip/Exclusive Opener fields to Creature Exceptions. 
                            Added first-run migration prompt. Removed obsolete check_for_badstuff and related logic.
             May 17, 2026 - Added check_dependencies at startup for all required suite scripts with correct authors.
             May 18, 2026 - Fixed GUI crash: get_val lambda now uses @combat_data directly.
             May 19, 2026 - Fixed groupeffects first-cast buffs firing only on enemy ship; now checks live NPC presence. All first-cast flags start false unconditionally. Fixed cast_spell_rapid_fire 
                            setting first-cast flag before confirming spell was castable.
             May 20, 2026 - Fixed cast_spell_society never setting $society_firstcast; signs/sigils/symbols now correctly flip to refresh-only path after first cast.
             May 20, 2026 - Looter now only runs when zero living hostile mobs remain in the room.
             May 22, 2026 - Applied mana_share_cooldown rate limiting to combat_spellup; buff casting now uses the same cooldown guard as can_cast_spell to prevent channel spam. Added Mana Request Cooldown field to General tab (default 90s).
             May 23, 2026 - Added Spell Sever tab with four spell number fields (sever_spell_1 through sever_spell_4).
             May 24, 2026 - Fixed targeting race conditions causing missed first encounters and mid-combat stalls. Targeting
                            responsibility moved out of load_attack_vars into get_target. get_target now called explicitly
                            before load_attack_vars in main loop and at top of combat. load_attack_vars returns early if
                            target is nil rather than blocking. Living/undead var switching still occurs each call.
             May 27, 2026 - Improved anti-poaching logic to prevent false positives causing combat stalls when hunting with
                            a companion. Disk check now cross-references Group.members by noun to forgive disks whose XML
                            hasn't caught up yet. Claim check uses a 3-strike counter to tolerate brief XML lag on room
                            entry. Added Claim::Lock wait to ensure claim state is fully settled before reading.
=end

